<h2 id="editors-notes">Editorâ€™s notes</h2>

<p>In this lesson, I show a practice tip on how you can transition between the chords of E, A, and B7 â€“ specifically by playing bass notes that walk up and down between these chords. This is a very common technique youâ€™ll find in lots of country music, especially from artists like Johnny Cash (e.g., Walk the Line) and Willie Nelson (e.g., Angel Flying Too Close to the Ground). Iâ€™ll show you the basics of how to play the chords used (E, A, and B7 â€“ including tabs) and then break down the fundamentals of this technique.</p>

